            {
              "s": ", persistent history and transcript, panel shell kept for overlay UX"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Slide Viewer"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — "
            },
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "c0c0c0c0-0080-0000-0000-000000000000"
              },
              {
                "s": "slide-view"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " Hob view renders attachments as navigable slides with zoom control. See "
            },
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "2168bea0-a118-4e5c-9de1-21a70f8a7bcf"
              },
              {
                "s": "Slide Viewer"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": "."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Hob stdlib: min/max"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — variadic "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "min"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " and "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "max"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " builtins added to the interpreter"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "19 of 41 views are Hob. JSON AST is canonical. The structural editor works. The kernel is minimal."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":hr"
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Priority 1: Reactive Transclusions"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Make transclusion mount points in "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "a1b2c3d4-5e6f-7a8b-9c0d-e1f2a3b4c5d6"
          },
          {
            "s": "hobson-markdown"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " subscribe to their source item's changes and re-render automatically. Currently transclusions render once — if the source item is edited, the embedding is stale until reload."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "This is the intersection of both the Structured Pages and Enhanced Markdown paths (see "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-0073-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "proposal"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "). The reactive infrastructure already exists (views use registry-based selector-filtered reactivity). The work is bounded: make each transclusion's rendered DOM listen for "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "item:updated"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " on the transcluded item ID, and re-render when it fires."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Directly improves the daily note-writing experience without requiring any design decisions about the page model or editor strategy."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Priority 2: Hob Correctness Fixes"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Two bugs discovered during slide-view development:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ol",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "`doseq` doesn't await async fns"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — the macro expands to "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "(do (map ...) nil)"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ", and "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "map"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " uses JS "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "Array.map"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " which doesn't await Hob's async functions. Any Hob view using "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "doseq"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " for side effects is silently broken. Fix: redefine "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "doseq"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " as a special form, or rewrite the macro to use "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "for"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": "."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "`dom-set!` doesn't support dotted paths"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "(dom-set! el :style.display \"none\")"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " sets a literal property named "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "\"style.display\""
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " instead of "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "el.style.display"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ". Workaround exists ("
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "(dom-set! (dom-get el :style) :display \"none\")"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ") but the dotted path is more ergonomic and less error-prone."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Deferred (Needs Further Thought)"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Structured Pages / Enhanced Markdown"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — "
            },
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "c0c0c0c0-0073-0000-0000-000000000000"
              },
              {
                "s": "The proposal"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " explores replacing markdown with Hob expressions vs enhancing the existing markdown system. The editor strategy is the key blocker — the structural editor is a prose regression, and the existing markdown + transclusion system is deeply used. Decision pending."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "External Data Import"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — an end-to-end import feature to validate the Type Workshop workflow. Deferred until a concrete import target is identified. See "
            },
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "c0c0c0c0-0042-0000-0000-000000000000"
              },
              {
                "s": "Future Directions § Part 2"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " for candidates."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":hr"
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "What's Not Here (and Why)"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
